reviewText: I have purchased every season of Grey's and have watched every episode. While some are better than others, what series does not have it's up's and down. I know that some years, the series will end & I surely want to see the final episode when it comes. I consider Grey's Anatomy to be a cross between a medical drama and a soap opera - but I find it very entertaining to watch.
summary: Grey's Anatomy has been an excellent series.

reviewText: This series just keeps getting better.  I was actually concerned about where it could go once the original characters finished their residency and how they could maintain interest as several of them left the show over the years.  I need not have worried.  The standards by and for this show have been held at the constant high level we have come to expect.  If you are one of the few who don't like the show or have never seen it, I am not going to put out any spoilers, except to say the indications are strong that there will be an eleventh season!  The only sad thing is I have to wait another year before I can own season ten.
Title: Grey's Anatomy: Season 9

reviewText: This is probably the best entertaining and tragic series that I have ever had the pleasure to watch. In fact I don't watch it on television, I buy the series every year because I can't imagine watching this extraordinary show with moments so harsh and shocking only to be interrupted by commercials or wait for the next week or next season talk about shrinking the....drama. I can't, the shock value is so much more when it's not interrupted plus you get all kinds of fun information on the actors on the characters and not to mention the bloopers and I love How Meredith Grey-Ellen's Pompeo's laugh is so great I start laughing and it's the same laugh in the bloopers as it is in the series and of course how can one outdo McDreamy, McSteamy, McBitchy, and George's famous McVomit....I have bought every years' series, and I will continue until one day some fool cancels it. But I will always have it. How would you like having a person like Cristina Yang..and their guest stars: Jeffrey Dean Morgan, Kyle Chandler, can you say a lot McYummies...but why of why must they always die...Jeffrey Dean Morgan is the dad in Supernatural ....and well let's not reveal anything for those Supernatural fans.... Love this show, the entire cast, and the genius who thought it up! There aren't enough stars in the sky to give to this super medical drama show. OOPs this is for series 1 to 8 I don't think nine is out yet? It won't matter because I will love it as much as loved each and every season. This is for all the seasons fans already know what happened from to 8 and I can't wait for season 9 (which I should have received by now) hint, hint
summary: Grey's Anatomy is here to stay for a long time
